name: Tupac
description:
Giclee print Paper size: 40x60cm
Mixed media on 310gsm William Turner – White, 100% watercolour cotton paper
Limited edition art prints of 13
Price: 1100 NOK Artist Anette Moi, a 28 year old illustrator, graphic designer and artist based in Stavanger, Norway. Moi finished her bachelor degree in graphic design last year at London Metropolotan Universty in England. Last year she had her first soloshow, “Funfair”, at Reedprojects Gallery in Stavanger, Norway. www.anettemoi.com Exhibition With the exhibition “Stars” Moi shows different portraits of musicians she listens to when she draws. Music is inspiring and important for Moi´s drawings. The portraits are Moi´s tribute to the real legends. Legends like Jimi Hendrix and Tupac are some of the stars that are portraited in the exhibition. See the "STARS" exhibition her

name: † M Ø R Π I Π G . G L Ø R Ψ †
description: Giclee print Paper size: 50x70cm / 19.6" x 27.5" Price: 800 NOK Artist Gustavo Bockos aka Vokos, is an art Director, Designer and illustrator based in São Paulo, Brazil. He does art Direction, advertising campaigns, fashion Photography and illustration for different clients and commissioned design work. Exhibition "Dirty Land" is an experimental contemporary pop culture exhibition. Through mixed media posters, adult content and known disney characters, Vokos awakens curiosity by the viewer. What was Walt Disney all about? Vokos was curious about what happened in Walt Disneys mind. After reading many lectures about Walt Disneys secret messages in his classical movies, Vokos wanted to show what could be behind an adult mind. See the "Dirty Land" exhibition her

name: Visceral Lettering
description: Original: Size: 53x76cm / 20.8" x 29.9" Ink and watercolor on aquarelle paper. Price: 6000 NOK Limited edition art prints of 10 Paper size: 50x70cm paper quality: 310gsm William Turner – White, 100% watercolour cotton paper. All prints are numbered and signed. Price: 1500 NOK Artist Sergio Haisch was born in La Paz, Bolivia 31 years ago; where, while studying media and communication, works as a reportage journalist. He moves to Norway in late 2003 and five years later he starts studying Graphic Design at Westerdals School of Communication. After finishing the regular two year study, he becomes part of the student-driven design agency Studio 3. Thereafter he starts freelancing and work with several different clients and projects, both as a graphic designer and as an illustrator. When he is not doing graphic design work, he works on his paintings. sergiohaisch.no

description:
Limited edition screenprint of 10 Size: 60x90cm Artwork Self-initiated project where old newspaper images were cut out, scanned and then put together again as a collage. The final images were silkscreened. A hommage to both old printing methods as well as digital exploration. All prints are signed. Price:500 NOK Artist Stig Nøstdahl Andersen / www.stigandersen.no
Stig Nøstdahl Andersen runs his own small business and shares office space with many fine and talented people. He have done that for the last five years. Having worked with many different types of customers, ranging from SOS-barnebyer to Slottsfjellfestivalen to the previous Tono logo. He loves to work with both print and web. In his life outside the office he has a nice little family, girlfriend and two children. Stig loves film, television, art, culture (high and low), music, skateboard (old school) and more. Like best to get up early, are fond of sweets and got wheat allergy. He Drinks one espresso coffee with hot milk and sugar every morning. Almost without exception. And he is starting to get gray hair.

name: glicée press (1/1) from an editorial illustration project for SYN & SEGN, ( 2 )
description:
Artist
Kristine Vintervold / kristinevintervold.no Kristine lives with Levi in ​​Oslo, where she works with illustration and concept development as a partner in Spinnovasjon AS.
She has a Bachelor's degree in Illustration from AUCB, UK. Kristine has the last ten years worked primarily with visual communication. In the intersection of innovation and visual communication Kristine wants to do something socially useful. Subtle solutions provide Kristine energy, how good they are measured in how much it makes her feel. Kristine may look quiet and cautious, but it is diametrically opposite. When Kristine was little she was stuttering. Door-to-door lottery ticket sales was the worst ultimate consequence of playing sports. Instead of standing there and stuttering "w.. we .., .. we will y ... you. purchase a ... a ...lottery ticket? "she took her little sister Anette with her. Kristine rang doorbells and her sister sold the lottery tickets. Kristine stutter no more, but the creative solutions still surrounds her. Artwork
glicée press (1/1) from an editorial illustration project for SYN & SEGN, 2012 Price: NOK 800, - ink. frame
